### Complexity Analysis

* **Time Complexity:** **`O(n² * 26)`**

  * We generate all possible substrings by choosing a starting index `i` and ending index `j`, which gives **`O(n²)`** combinations.

  * For each substring, we update the frequency in constant time.

  * The `isPossible()` function scans all 26 characters → **`O(26)`**.


* **Space Complexity:** **`O(26)`**

  * A frequency array of size 26 is maintained for each starting index.

  * No additional space proportional to `n` is used.

  * Hence, space remains constant.


## Solution 2 - Optimal Approach

### Intuition

* A substring is valid if at least one character appears at least `threshold` times

* Instead of checking all substrings, use a sliding window to maintain frequencies dynamically

* Once a window becomes valid, any extension of it will also remain valid

* This allows counting multiple substrings at once instead of checking individually


### Approach

* Use two pointers to maintain a window and a frequency array for characters

* Expand the window by moving the right pointer and updating frequency

* When the condition is satisfied, shrink the window from the left to find minimal valid window

* For each valid state, add `(n - i)` to the answer to count all possible extensions efficiently

### Pseudo Code

<CodeBlock language={customtext} showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle={Normal Code}>

```text
countResonantClips(recording, threshold) {
    /*
       recording is a string of length n
       Use sliding window to count substrings where
       at least one character appears >= threshold times
    */
    n = length of recording
    start = 0
    ans = 0
    /* Frequency array for 26 lowercase letters */
    freq = array of size 26 initialized to 0
    /* Expand window using end pointer */
    for (i from 0 to n - 1) {
        /* Add current character to window */
        ch = recording[i]
        freq[ch - 'a'] = freq[ch - 'a'] + 1
        /* Shrink window while condition is satisfied */
        while (isPossible(freq, threshold)) {
            /* Remove leftmost character */
            leftChar = recording[start]
            freq[leftChar - 'a'] = freq[leftChar - 'a'] - 1
            start = start + 1
            /* All substrings from current window to end are valid */
            ans = ans + (n - i)
        }
    }
    return ans
}

isPossible(freq, k) {
    /* Check if any character frequency >= k */
    for (i from 0 to 25) {
        if (freq[i] >= k) {
            return true
        }
    }
    return false
}
