# Convert Doubly Linked List to Array

## Solution 1

### Intuition

* The given node can be anywhere in the doubly linked list, so we need to reconstruct the full list from that point

* Since each node has both `prev` and `next`, we can traverse in both directions to collect all elements

* Left side traversal will give elements in reverse order, so it must be corrected

* Combining left side, current node, and right side gives the full list in proper order


### Approach

* Traverse towards the left using `prev` pointer and store elements in a list

* Traverse towards the right using `next` pointer and store elements in another list

* Reverse the left list to maintain correct sequence from head to current node

* Merge left list, current node value, and right list into the final array and return it


### Pseudo Code

<CodeBlock language={customtext} showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle={Normal Code}>

```text
toArray(node) {
    /*
       Given a node in a doubly linked list,
       convert the entire list into an array
    */
    list1 = empty list   /* stores left side */
    list2 = empty list   /* stores right side */
    /* Traverse towards left using prev pointer */
    node1 = node.prev
    while (node1 is not NULL) {
        add node1.data to list1
        node1 = node1.prev
    }
    /* Traverse towards right using next pointer */
    node2 = node.next
    while (node2 is not NULL) {
        add node2.data to list2
        node2 = node2.next
    }
    /* Reverse left list to maintain correct order */
    reverse(list1)
    ans = empty list
    /* Add left part */
    for (each value x in list1) {
        add x to ans
    }
    /* Add current node */
    add node.data to ans
    /* Add right part */
    for (each value x in list2) {
        add x to ans
    }
    return ans
}
```

