# Longest Self-Contained Substring


## Solution1 - Brute Force Approach

### Intuition

* A segment is valid only when every character that appears inside it is completely contained in that segment. So if a character appears inside, none of its occurrences should remain outside.

* To check this easily for any segment, the solution first stores how many times each character appears in the whole string, and also builds prefix counts to quickly know how many times that character appears inside any chosen segment.

* Then it tries every possible segment `[left, right]` except the whole string itself.

* For each segment, if every character that appears inside has its full total count inside the segment, then that segment is valid. Among all such valid segments, we keep the maximum length.

### Approach

* Build a prefix frequency table for all `26` lowercase letters, so we can quickly count how many times any character appears inside any segment.

* Also store the total frequency of each character in the whole string.

* Try every possible segment `[left, right]` using two loops.

* Skip the segment if its length is equal to the full string length, because the valid segment must be a proper substring.

* For the current segment, check all `26` characters.

* For each character, find how many times it appears inside the segment using the prefix table.

* If a character appears inside the segment, but its inside count is smaller than its total count in the whole string, then some occurrence of that character lies outside the segment, so this segment is invalid.

* If all characters satisfy the condition, update the answer with the segment length.

* After checking all segments, return the maximum valid length, or `-1` if none exists.

### Pseudo Code

<CodeBlock language={customtext} showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle={Normal Code}>

```text
longestExclusiveSegment(text) {
    n = length of text
    /* Create prefix frequency table for all 26 lowercase letters */
    pref = 2D list of size 26 x (n + 1) filled with 0
    /* Create total frequency array for the whole string */
    total = list of size 26 filled with 0
    /* Build prefix counts and total counts */
    for (i = 0 to n - 1) {
        /* Copy previous prefix counts for all characters */
        for (ch = 0 to 25) {
            pref[ch][i + 1] = pref[ch][i]
        }
        /* Increase count of current character */
        idx = text[i] - 'a'
        pref[idx][i + 1] = pref[idx][i + 1] + 1
        total[idx] = total[idx] + 1
    }
    /* Store the best valid segment length found so far */
    answer = -1
    /* Try every possible starting index */
    for (left = 0 to n - 1) {
        /* Try every possible ending index */
        for (right = left to n - 1) {
            /* Compute current segment length */
            length = right - left + 1
            /* Skip if this segment is the whole string */
            if (length == n) {
                continue
            }
            /* Assume current segment is valid */
            valid = true
            /* Check all 26 characters */
            for (ch = 0 to 25) {
                /* Count how many times this character appears inside [left, right] */
                inside = pref[ch][right + 1] - pref[ch][left]
                /* If character appears inside but not all its occurrences are inside, segment is invalid */
                if (inside > 0 and inside != total[ch]) {
                    valid = false
                    break
                }
            }
            /* If segment is valid, update the maximum length */
            if (valid) {
                answer = maximum of answer and length
            }
        }
    }
    /* Return the longest valid proper segment */
    return answer
}
