# Count Values With Distinct Digits


## Solution 1 - Digit Frequency Check

### Intuition

* We need to count how many numbers in the range have all digits different, so the direct idea is to check every number one by one.

* For each number, we look at its digits and keep track of how many times each digit appears.

* If any digit appears more than once, that number is not a distinct-digit number.

* If all digits appear at most once, we count that number as valid. After checking the whole range, we get the final answer.

### Approach

* Traverse every number from `startVal` to `endVal`.

* For each number, check whether all its digits are distinct.

* To do this, keep a frequency array of size `10` for digits `0` to `9`.

* Extract digits one by one using modulo and division.

* If any digit is seen more than once, stop early and mark that number as invalid.

* If the full number is processed without any repeated digit, count it as a valid distinct-digit number.

* After checking all numbers in the range, return the total count.


### Pseudo Code

<CodeBlock language={customtext} showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle={Normal Code}>

```text
isDistinctDigit(num) {
    freq = list of size 10 filled with 0
    /* Extract digits one by one until the number becomes 0 */
    while (num > 0) {
        /* Take the last digit */
        digit = num % 10
        /* Increase frequency of this digit */
        freq[digit] = freq[digit] + 1
        /* If this digit appears more than once, number is invalid */
        if (freq[digit] > 1) {
            return false
        }
        /* Remove the last digit from the number */
        num = num / 10
    }
    /* If no digit repeats, number is valid */
    return true
}

distinctCount(startVal, endVal) {
    count = 0
    /* Check every number in the range */
    for (num = startVal to endVal) {
        /* If current number has all distinct digits, count it */
        if (isDistinctDigit(num)) {
            count = count + 1
        }
    }
    /* Return the final count */
    return count
}
